[{"id":"VR857474","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Figure 1 and 2 are shown. Figure 1 shows a smooth reflecting sphere. At the center of the sphere, a positive x and positive y axis are shown. Ray 1 originates from the left of the sphere and travels horizontally striking the upper left edge of the sphere. A dash line is shown starting from where Ray 1 strikes the sphere towards the origin of the x-y axis. The dash line makes an angle of 45 degrees with the horizontal x axis.  Ray 2 originates from the right side of the figure and travels horizontally striking the upper right edge of the sphere. A dash line is shown starting from where the Ray 2 strikes the sphere towards the center of the x-y axis. The dash line makes an angle of 45 degrees with the horizontal x axis. Ray 3 originates from the lower right of the figure and travels slanted upwards to the left. Ray 3 strikes the right edge of the sphere at a point on the x axis. Ray 3 makes an angle of 45 degrees with the dash line normal to the surface of the sphere.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857474.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A sphere has a smooth surface from which incident light rays are reflected. Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> shows the sphere and three incident rays, rays <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, along with a pair of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x y\"><math alttext=\"x y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-coordinate axes with its origin at the center of the sphere. Rays <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> are each parallel to the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-axis, and Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> is directed at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"45 degrees\"><math alttext=\"45 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span> to the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-axis as shown. Which of the following ranks the angles <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 3\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></span></span> between each reflected ray and the positive <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction for rays <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, respectively? The angle between a reflected ray and the positive <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction is defined as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> for two rays.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857474_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1 equals theta sub 2, which equals theta sub 3\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1 equals theta sub 2, which equals theta sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, theta sub 1 equals theta sub 2, close parenthesis, which is greater than theta sub 3\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, theta sub 1 equals theta sub 2, close parenthesis, which is greater than theta sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1 is greater than theta sub 2, which is greater than theta sub 3\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1 is greater than theta sub 2, which is greater than theta sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2 is greater than theta sub 3, which is greater than theta sub 1 \"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2 is greater than theta sub 3, which is greater than theta sub 1 \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]